text: Walford is a city in Iowa in the United States. It is part of Benton County and is a small rural city. Walford is the second largest city in its state. As of 2022, nearly all of the population were U.S. citizens with 99.8%, however, the rate of citizenship is decreasing. Some of the most commonly reported ancestry of the population were German, Irish, English, Czech, and Norwegian ancestries. == References == Category:Cities in Iowa
title: Walford, Iowa
